&lt;strong&gt;Background&lt;/strong&gt;

In September 1995 FMG was one of the earliest fund companies to launch a Russia fund. Russia is the largest oil producer in the world, producing an average of 10.3 million barrels of oil per day, totaling an average of 3.8 billion barrels a year. It produces 12.9% of the world’s oil and has 25% of the natural gas production.

&lt;strong&gt;Russia at a Glance&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Equities are trading at very low valuations&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;•   One of the largest and fastest growing consumer markets&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;•   Solid balance sheet and very low public debt&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;•   Unique geographic position and vast natural resources&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&amp;nbsp;

&lt;strong&gt;Russia is Moving Up!&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Despite massive swings in the key Russian commodity, namely crude oil, Russian equities were able to produce a stellar return of 14% for the first three months of the year.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Largest positions are in blue chips such as Lukoil, Sberbank, Gazprom and Rosneft.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&amp;nbsp;

&lt;strong&gt;FUND DESCRIPTION&lt;/strong&gt;

The investment objective of the Russian Federation First Mercantile Fund is to achieve long term capital appreciation utilizing a concentrated sector strategy investment approach. The Fund Manager has significant experience gained over many years of investing in Russian companies.

&amp;nbsp;

The Fund invests mainly in shares of companies with short and long term profit opportunities fuelled by export and domestic consumption and investment within Russia. Fundamental analysis is utilized to source attractively priced companies with significant earnings potential, while a quantitative technical model to determine allocations could be applied from time to time.

&amp;nbsp;

The Fund can invest in a wide ranging sector of large and medium sized value- and growth-oriented companies and it also offers investors efficient access to the Russian stock market. Risk management and fund liquidity is an integral element of the portfolio management process, while the fund is well diversified geographically and among different industry sectors. The opportunistic nature of the fund targets investors with a higher risk-reward return profile, and who wish to tap into the world’s largest oil producer.

&amp;nbsp;

The Russian Federation First Mercantile Fund offers investors direct and efficient access to the Russian stock market.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=&quot;1/1&quot;][vc_column_text css_animation=&quot;&quot;]
